packet flow:
  opening window:
    held_item_slot of name tag (0, aka first hand slot)
    use_item (increment last sequence (starting at 0, first packet is 1) +1 (sequence increases every use_item packet))
    get windowid from open_window (will likely just be 1 no matter what, 0 for inventory)
    wait for window_items with corresponding windowid (1)
  
  selecting maps:
    use data from window_items to figure out what slot each map selection is
    repeat for each map:
      window_click on corresponding windowid and slot, using mode 0 (normal click) and getting stateid (The last received State ID from either a Set Container Slot or a Set Container Content packet) https://minecraft.wiki/w/Java_Edition_protocol/Packets#Click_Container
      wait until recieved chat message confirming voting or complaining about cooldown, if complain then wait a bit and try again
      repeat for each map
  
  closing window:
    literally just send close_window packet with corresponding window id

extra:
  either forward the packets to the user so the window opens and they stop moving OR suppress all outgoing movement data in a buffer until the voting is done
